WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.689 --> 00:00:07.374
- In the criminal justice
system.

2
00:00:07.441 --> 00:00:08.809
the people are represented

3
00:00:08.842 --> 00:00:11.236
by two separate.
yet equally important groups:

4
00:00:11.303 --> 00:00:13.071
the police.
who investigate crime.

5
00:00:13.171 --> 00:00:15.974
and the district attorneys.
who prosecute the offenders.

6
00:00:16.008 --> 00:00:18.810
These are their stories.

7
00:00:18.844 --> 00:00:22.247
- And now. the moment
we've all been waiting for.

8
00:00:22.347 --> 00:00:25.292
Please welcome our
final two contestants

9
00:00:25.359 --> 00:00:27.261
for Miss New York Metro.

10
00:00:29.763 --> 00:00:33.500
I know how hard it is for these
young women to stand up here.

11
00:00:33.567 --> 00:00:36.194
I was in their shoes
just a few years ago

12
00:00:36.261 --> 00:00:38.772
and I am honored
to be back to judge.

13
00:00:38.872 --> 00:00:43.510
To many of you. this pageant
may seem like a zero-sum game.

14
00:00:43.544 --> 00:00:47.080
but it's really about
connection and sisterhood.

15
00:00:47.147 --> 00:00:51.685
Tonight. however.
we do have to pick a winner.

16
00:00:51.752 --> 00:00:53.987
Our first runner-up is...

17
00:00:54.054 --> 00:00:56.356
Miss Prospect Heights.

18
00:00:56.423 --> 00:01:02.162
making our Miss New York Metro
2026. Miss Astoria!

19
00:01:12.798 --> 00:01:16.201
Remember. we're all winners.

20
00:01:20.238 --> 00:01:23.283
- They held the Miss New York
Metro pageant here last night.

21
00:01:23.350 --> 00:01:25.477
- She a contestant?
- No. a judge.

22
00:01:25.544 --> 00:01:27.354
Janitor found her this morning.

23
00:01:27.487 --> 00:01:29.039
- Oh.

24
00:01:32.025 --> 00:01:33.043
♪ ♪

25
00:01:33.076 --> 00:01:34.252
Katie Harrington.

26
00:01:34.319 --> 00:01:36.346
age 29.

27
00:01:38.256 --> 00:01:40.267
Looks like she also works
at the local news station.

28
00:01:41.902 --> 00:01:43.537
- Must have hit
the carotid artery.

29
00:01:43.670 --> 00:01:45.722
- Yeah. she bled out fast.

30
00:01:45.756 --> 00:01:47.165
- You got a time of death?

31
00:01:47.265 --> 00:01:49.142
- MLI said.
based on temp and rigidity.

32
00:01:49.209 --> 00:01:50.544
between 10:00 and 11:00 p.m.

33
00:01:50.610 --> 00:01:52.212
- All right.

34
00:01:52.312 --> 00:01:54.281
Well. let's make sure we get
the scissors dusted for prints.

35
00:01:54.348 --> 00:01:56.216
Any witnesses?
- None.

36
00:01:56.249 --> 00:01:57.918
Place had pretty much
cleared out by that time.

37
00:01:57.985 --> 00:02:00.087
- What about the security
camera situation?

38
00:02:00.153 --> 00:02:03.290
- Far as we know. no cameras
in the dressing room.

39
00:02:03.390 --> 00:02:05.058
- Well. I always heard
these beauty pageants

40
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:07.077
were cutthroat. but...

41
00:02:13.859 --> 00:02:20.891
♪ ♪

42
00:02:57.736 --> 00:03:00.447
- You turned off
all of the cameras?

43
00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:02.282
- We had 30 women
backstage last night

44
00:03:02.315 --> 00:03:03.784
in various states of undress.

45
00:03:03.817 --> 00:03:05.085
They wanted privacy.

46
00:03:05.152 --> 00:03:06.686
- What about security guards?

47
00:03:06.753 --> 00:03:08.055
- One guard was
posted backstage.

48
00:03:08.121 --> 00:03:09.656
- He see anything?

49
00:03:09.723 --> 00:03:11.258
- Apparently he was
FaceTiming with his girlfriend

50
00:03:11.358 --> 00:03:12.926
at the end of the night.

51
00:03:13.026 --> 00:03:14.694
It's usually an uneventful job.

52
00:03:14.761 --> 00:03:15.987
We can barely fill
an audience these days.

53
00:03:16.021 --> 00:03:17.130
- Why is that?

54
00:03:17.197 --> 00:03:18.256
- Too much competition--

55
00:03:18.323 --> 00:03:19.658
YouTube. social media.

56
00:03:19.691 --> 00:03:23.737
- So there are
fewer pageants these days?

57
00:03:23.804 --> 00:03:25.272
- Well. there used
to be ten a year.

58
00:03:25.338 --> 00:03:26.506
Now there were two.

59
00:03:26.573 --> 00:03:29.042
- That really puts extra
pressure on the contestants.

60
00:03:29.109 --> 00:03:31.044
- And on the judges.
- For sure.

61
00:03:31.111 --> 00:03:33.180
Beauty pageants are still
important to these people--

62
00:03:33.246 --> 00:03:36.333
some of these girls. if they
lose. think their life is over.

63
00:03:36.366 --> 00:03:40.178
- We're gonna need a list
of last night's contestants.

64
00:03:40.212 --> 00:03:42.289
- I'm surprised these
pageants are still a thing.

65
00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:43.824
I mean. I thought
we were way past that.

66
00:03:43.857 --> 00:03:46.159
- Yeah. I gave up
on those years ago.

67
00:03:46.193 --> 00:03:49.830
- Hey. video just landed
from outside the theater.

68
00:03:49.863 --> 00:03:51.665
Picked up someone
running out the exit

69
00:03:51.698 --> 00:03:53.400
by the dressing room at 10:25.

70
00:03:55.302 --> 00:03:56.770
- Can you freeze it there?

71
00:03:56.870 --> 00:03:59.039
Not enough of the face
visible for facial rec?

72
00:03:59.072 --> 00:04:01.032
- No.
- That hat.

73
00:04:01.066 --> 00:04:02.676
What is that stitching?

74
00:04:02.742 --> 00:04:04.444
- Looks like they
got it turned inside out

75
00:04:04.511 --> 00:04:07.681
to hide the monogram or
something--what is that. XLV?

76
00:04:07.714 --> 00:04:09.141
- Yeah. I don't think
it's a brand.

77
00:04:09.207 --> 00:04:10.475
Maybe Roman numerals?

78
00:04:10.575 --> 00:04:12.252
- Do we have any other video
of this person entering?

79
00:04:12.319 --> 00:04:13.754
- No. and it was
freezing that day.

80
00:04:13.820 --> 00:04:16.022
so half the people entering the
theater were wearing beanies.

81
00:04:16.156 --> 00:04:19.025
But I have some good news.

82
00:04:19.159 --> 00:04:23.630
Found this interesting text
from a Kailani Arizaga.

83
00:04:23.730 --> 00:04:27.701
"Be careful how you vote.
There are consequences."

84
00:04:27.734 --> 00:04:29.569
- Sounds like a threat to me.

85
00:04:29.636 --> 00:04:31.772
- That name rings a bell.
Hold on.

86
00:04:34.941 --> 00:04:36.076
Yeah. here.

87
00:04:36.143 --> 00:04:39.104
"Kailani Arizaga.
Miss Prospect Heights."

88
00:04:39.171 --> 00:04:40.697
She was the first runner-up.

89
00:04:43.884 --> 00:04:46.219
- I've known Katie
since I was 15.

90
00:04:46.286 --> 00:04:49.356
She was like an older sister.
a mentor.

91
00:04:49.422 --> 00:04:50.849
- So you liked her?

92
00:04:50.916 --> 00:04:52.425
- Loved her.

93
00:04:52.492 --> 00:04:54.628
- Well. why did you send her
that threatening text

94
00:04:54.728 --> 00:04:57.798
last night--the one that said
there'd be consequences

95
00:04:57.864 --> 00:04:59.065
if she didn't vote
the right way?

96
00:04:59.099 --> 00:05:01.268
- What are you talking about?

97
00:05:01.301 --> 00:05:03.762
- This one.

98
00:05:03.795 --> 00:05:05.172
- No. you got it wrong.

99
00:05:05.272 --> 00:05:07.699
I wanted her to vote
for someone else.

100
00:05:07.766 --> 00:05:08.942
- You wanted to lose?

101
00:05:08.975 --> 00:05:10.544
- I wanted to not win.

102
00:05:10.610 --> 00:05:12.012
- Why'd you do it
in the first place?

103
00:05:12.078 --> 00:05:13.780
- My mom.

104
00:05:13.814 --> 00:05:15.715
These pageants mean
everything to her.

105
00:05:15.782 --> 00:05:18.251
She says they can open doors.
maybe even get me

106
00:05:18.285 --> 00:05:20.212
a scholarship for grad school.

107
00:05:20.312 --> 00:05:21.479
- Can you tell us
where you were last night

108
00:05:21.546 --> 00:05:22.689
after the pageant?

109
00:05:22.756 --> 00:05:26.359
- Eating pizza
for the first time in a year.

110
00:05:26.459 --> 00:05:27.761
- Got anybody
who can back that up?

111
00:05:27.861 --> 00:05:30.622
- Yeah. a few classmates.

112
00:05:30.655 --> 00:05:33.099
Kinda turned into a party.

113
00:05:33.133 --> 00:05:34.784
I asked Katie
if she wanted to join.

114
00:05:34.818 --> 00:05:37.170
but she said she couldn't.

115
00:05:38.663 --> 00:05:40.073
- We gotta go.

116
00:05:40.173 --> 00:05:41.875
Katie's dad just got in
from Alabama.

117
00:05:41.942 --> 00:05:43.109
-

118
00:05:43.143 --> 00:05:44.177
Thank you.

119
00:05:48.073 --> 00:05:51.184
- I still remember the day
I helped Katie move in here.

120
00:05:54.479 --> 00:05:57.182
Her mom had just passed.

121
00:05:57.249 --> 00:05:59.960
Katie wanted to stay at home.
look after me. of course.

122
00:06:00.093 --> 00:06:01.628
but. uh.

123
00:06:01.728 --> 00:06:04.197
I told her
she had to follow her dreams.

124
00:06:05.899 --> 00:06:08.301
Just knew she was
meant for great things.

125
00:06:08.335 --> 00:06:11.404
- Mr. Harrington. were you
and your daughter very close?

126
00:06:11.471 --> 00:06:12.472
- Yeah.

127
00:06:12.505 --> 00:06:14.307
We talked every day.

128
00:06:14.441 --> 00:06:16.935
- Was she having any problems
with anyone?

129
00:06:17.002 --> 00:06:18.545
Friends? A boyfriend?

130
00:06:18.612 --> 00:06:22.549
- She was always too busy with
work for much of a social life.

131
00:06:25.110 --> 00:06:27.721
I encouraged her to date.
Didn't want her to be lonely.

132
00:06:32.292 --> 00:06:35.195
You know.
there was this one guy.

133
00:06:35.262 --> 00:06:38.898
kept chasing after her
like a damn dog with a bone.

134
00:06:38.965 --> 00:06:40.734
- He got a name?
- I never made it that far.

135
00:06:40.800 --> 00:06:45.138
Never even went out on a date.
but he was persistent.

136
00:06:45.205 --> 00:06:47.407
Kept calling her
and sending her flowers.

137
00:06:47.507 --> 00:06:49.643
Got a bit much for Katie.
if I'm being honest.

138
00:06:49.709 --> 00:06:51.611
- Do you know where he worked?

139
00:06:51.711 --> 00:06:53.947
How they met?
Any detail will help.

140
00:06:54.047 --> 00:06:56.616
- They met at some sort
of cancer fundraiser.

141
00:06:56.683 --> 00:06:57.951
and he was a hockey player.

142
00:06:58.018 --> 00:06:58.952
That's all I know.

143
00:06:59.019 --> 00:07:01.121
♪ ♪

144
00:07:01.187 --> 00:07:02.522
- Any luck with
the hockey player?

145
00:07:02.622 --> 00:07:04.357
- Yeah. I checked out
Katie's Instagram.

146
00:07:04.391 --> 00:07:06.026
Looks like the only
cancer fundraiser

147
00:07:06.059 --> 00:07:07.427
she attended in
the last six months

148
00:07:07.527 --> 00:07:10.463
was the United Hands
Leukemia Gala.

149
00:07:10.563 --> 00:07:13.558
Lots of photos of her and this
guy named Alexander Hayes.

150
00:07:13.591 --> 00:07:14.659
- Looks smitten.

151
00:07:14.759 --> 00:07:16.136
Hockey player?

152
00:07:16.236 --> 00:07:18.905
- Rookie left-winger for New
York's favorite hockey team.

153
00:07:18.938 --> 00:07:20.173
- Islanders?

154
00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:21.708
- Not funny.

155
00:07:21.841 --> 00:07:23.343
- No choir boy.

156
00:07:23.410 --> 00:07:24.602
He just finished
a five-game suspension

157
00:07:24.669 --> 00:07:26.771
for smashing a stick
into his opponent's head.

158
00:07:26.838 --> 00:07:27.914
- And here's the best part--

159
00:07:27.981 --> 00:07:31.609
he posted a story last night
at 9:30 p.m.

160
00:07:31.676 --> 00:07:35.071
Location tag puts him two
blocks away from the pageant.

161
00:07:43.697 --> 00:07:43.922
.

162
00:07:44.030 --> 00:07:46.599
- I adored Katie.
I would never hurt her.

163
00:07:46.666 --> 00:07:49.627
- Well. you say adored.
We say stalked.

164
00:07:49.694 --> 00:07:50.804
- We talked to her doorman.

165
00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:52.238
We know that you were
sending her flowers.

166
00:07:52.272 --> 00:07:53.598
hanging outside her building.

167
00:07:53.631 --> 00:07:54.966
- Yeah. to--to show her
that I liked her.

168
00:07:55.033 --> 00:07:56.476
that I was serious
about dating her.

169
00:07:56.543 --> 00:07:59.938
- She had two extra deadbolts
installed in her door.

170
00:07:59.971 --> 00:08:02.307
- Look. I was just
trying to get a date.

171
00:08:02.374 --> 00:08:03.750
It's called being romantic.

172
00:08:03.883 --> 00:08:05.643
- If she said yes.
it's romantic.

173
00:08:05.710 --> 00:08:07.253
If she said no. it's scary.

174
00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:08.780
- So what happened. hmm?

175
00:08:08.813 --> 00:08:09.889
You get tired of
waiting for her

176
00:08:09.956 --> 00:08:11.257
to see how romantic you were?

177
00:08:11.291 --> 00:08:12.984
Maybe you snuck into her
dressing room last night?

178
00:08:13.051 --> 00:08:13.994
- What?

179
00:08:14.060 --> 00:08:14.986
- We know you were
near the theater

180
00:08:15.053 --> 00:08:16.129
where the pageant was held.

181
00:08:16.162 --> 00:08:17.530
- Right around the time
of the murder.

182
00:08:17.597 --> 00:08:18.932
- Hey. look. you guys
are crazy. all right?

183
00:08:18.965 --> 00:08:21.234
I was at a party last night
with about 200 other people

184
00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:23.002
and I was there
until about midnight.

185
00:08:23.069 --> 00:08:25.372
Instead of wasting your time
talking to me.

186
00:08:25.438 --> 00:08:27.440
you should look into
the shady people

187
00:08:27.474 --> 00:08:29.067
she was dealing with at work.

188
00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:30.168
- What does that mean?

189
00:08:30.235 --> 00:08:31.511
- She told me that
as a journalist

190
00:08:31.611 --> 00:08:33.246
she had to take big swings.
to go where her colleagues

191
00:08:33.346 --> 00:08:34.514
were too scared to go.

192
00:08:34.581 --> 00:08:36.649
So if she was adding
extra locks to her door.

193
00:08:36.683 --> 00:08:39.786
I mean. it's because of that.
not because of me.

194
00:08:39.853 --> 00:08:42.605
You should go talk to her boss.

195
00:08:46.760 --> 00:08:48.762
- I wouldn't call her
segments dangerous.

196
00:08:48.828 --> 00:08:50.096
More like ambitious.

197
00:08:50.163 --> 00:08:51.965
She was a smart woman.
had a great gut instinct.

198
00:08:52.098 --> 00:08:53.299
knew how to avoid trouble.

199
00:08:53.433 --> 00:08:54.701
- Sounds like
you knew her well.

200
00:08:54.768 --> 00:08:55.735
- Well. I took her
under my wing

201
00:08:55.802 --> 00:08:56.986
when she first started here.

202
00:08:57.020 --> 00:08:58.538
I got her out from
behind the research desk.

203
00:08:58.605 --> 00:09:00.140
made her a field reporter.

204
00:09:00.273 --> 00:09:02.909
I was a producer on
some of her segments.

205
00:09:03.009 --> 00:09:04.244
- Very nice of you.

206
00:09:04.344 --> 00:09:06.046
- Well. it's a tough business
for women here.

207
00:09:06.112 --> 00:09:09.382
so I thought I could help
wherever possible.

208
00:09:09.449 --> 00:09:10.917
- If you don't mind.
when was the last time

209
00:09:11.017 --> 00:09:12.419
you spoke to Katie?

210
00:09:12.519 --> 00:09:16.122
- Um. she was in the office
until about 5:30 last night

211
00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:18.258
and then headed downtown
to the pageant.

212
00:09:18.324 --> 00:09:19.726
- Did you speak to her
after that?

213
00:09:19.793 --> 00:09:21.795
- No. I stayed working
for a few more hours

214
00:09:21.895 --> 00:09:23.163
and then I went home.

215
00:09:23.229 --> 00:09:24.856
- And you were there all night?

216
00:09:25.899 --> 00:09:27.834
Sorry. just standard procedure.

217
00:09:27.901 --> 00:09:29.402
You know. the more people
we can eliminate

218
00:09:29.469 --> 00:09:30.603
from her life. the better.

219
00:09:30.703 --> 00:09:32.739
- Right.
Of course. I wanna be helpful.

220
00:09:32.806 --> 00:09:34.074
Yes. I was home all night.

221
00:09:35.809 --> 00:09:39.012
Here is her work schedule.

222
00:09:39.045 --> 00:09:40.138
I hope it's helpful.

223
00:09:40.205 --> 00:09:41.531
- We will take a look.

224
00:09:41.564 --> 00:09:44.642
- Do you know. did she have
a work phone of any sort?

225
00:09:44.742 --> 00:09:46.853
- Yes. she had several.

226
00:09:46.986 --> 00:09:49.214
Good reporters
always use burners

227
00:09:49.247 --> 00:09:51.658
to protect their sources.

228
00:09:51.758 --> 00:09:54.961
Katie was a terrific reporter.

229
00:09:55.061 --> 00:09:56.721
She was gonna do great things.

230
00:10:00.917 --> 00:10:02.469
- Hey.

231
00:10:02.535 --> 00:10:04.387
Warrant for the burner phones
came through.

232
00:10:04.420 --> 00:10:05.505
- And?

233
00:10:05.605 --> 00:10:08.433
- And we got a pretty
interesting text.

234
00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:09.767
"This is not okay.

235
00:10:09.834 --> 00:10:12.011
Make this right or things
are gonna get ugly."

236
00:10:12.078 --> 00:10:13.713
- Any luck ID'ing the sender?

237
00:10:13.847 --> 00:10:16.182
- Phone's registered
to a Jazmin Hernandez.

238
00:10:16.282 --> 00:10:17.942
She's affiliated
with the Cobra 10 gang.

239
00:10:18.009 --> 00:10:19.577
Got a pretty healthy
rap sheet. too--

240
00:10:19.611 --> 00:10:21.921
drugs. assault.
weapons charges.

241
00:10:21.988 --> 00:10:23.456
- Let's go talk to her.

242
00:10:27.393 --> 00:10:29.746
- Yeah. that's me.

243
00:10:29.779 --> 00:10:31.564
I meant it too.

244
00:10:31.598 --> 00:10:33.458
- Could you be more specific?

245
00:10:33.525 --> 00:10:35.435
- Katie came up here
a few months ago

246
00:10:35.468 --> 00:10:39.138
with that other news lady.
Ann Merrick.

247
00:10:39.205 --> 00:10:41.407
They convinced me to help them
do a segment

248
00:10:41.474 --> 00:10:44.202
showing gangs
recruiting young girls.

249
00:10:44.302 --> 00:10:46.746
- So you were a source?

250
00:10:46.779 --> 00:10:49.607
- I connected her
to the right people.

251
00:10:49.641 --> 00:10:52.101
- Doesn't explain
the angry text. though.

252
00:10:52.135 --> 00:10:53.720
- When the segment came out
a few weeks ago.

253
00:10:53.786 --> 00:10:55.488
there was a mistake.

254
00:10:55.555 --> 00:10:58.858
A guy that lives here. he was
in some of the video they shot.

255
00:10:58.925 --> 00:11:01.127
They claimed
he was a gang member.

256
00:11:01.194 --> 00:11:04.622
He was pissed. and now people
are coming after me about it.

257
00:11:06.332 --> 00:11:07.734
- All right. well. can you tell
us where you were

258
00:11:07.834 --> 00:11:10.036
last night around 10:00?

259
00:11:10.103 --> 00:11:13.006
- Working the register
at a bodega.

260
00:11:13.106 --> 00:11:15.141
166th and Webster.

261
00:11:15.175 --> 00:11:16.968
They got cameras everywhere
if you wanna check.

262
00:11:23.783 --> 00:11:26.144
So. am I good?
- For now.

263
00:11:28.621 --> 00:11:31.349
Where did you get that hat?

264
00:11:31.416 --> 00:11:32.959
- Ann Merrick gave it to me.

265
00:11:36.087 --> 00:11:38.423
♪ ♪

266
00:11:38.489 --> 00:11:39.299
- All right.

267
00:11:39.432 --> 00:11:41.568
Yep. thank you.

268
00:11:41.634 --> 00:11:43.803
Turns out Ann Merrick
had those beanies made

269
00:11:43.836 --> 00:11:45.697
for the station's anniversary.

270
00:11:45.763 --> 00:11:46.806
- Okay.

271
00:11:46.839 --> 00:11:48.766
Ann told us that
she went home after work

272
00:11:48.833 --> 00:11:50.677
